==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[Achillis tendo]]'', a term devised by the Dutch anatomist [[w:Philip Verheyden|Philip Verheyden]] in 1693 in reference to the mythological account of [[Achilles]] being held by the heel when dipped in the [[w:Styx|River Styx]]

===Noun===
'''[[Achilles]]’ [[tendon]]'''

# {{anatomy}} The strong [[tendon]] formed of the united tendons of the large [[muscle]]s in the [[calf]] of the leg, an inserted into the bone of the heel.

====Synonyms====
* [[calcaneal tendon]]
* [[tendo Achillis]]
* [[tendo calcaneus]]

